<i>adverb</i>: 정당히 [정ː당히], 이만저만 [이만저만], 웬만큼 [웬ː만큼], 엄정히 [엄정히], 어지간히 [어지간히], 십상 [십쌍], 상당히 [상당히], 무던히 [무던히], 당연히 [당연히], 꽤 [꽤], 깨끗이 [깨끄시], 공평히 [공평히], 공정히 [공정히], 공명정대히 [공명정대히] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>정당히 [정ː당히]</dt><br>
<dd>fairly</dd><br>
<dd>이치에 맞아 올바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>Reasonably and righteously.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>이만저만 [이만저만]</dt><br>
<dd>tolerably; bearably; fairly</dd><br>
<dd>상태나 성질 등이 짐작하거나 다스릴 수 있을 정도로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which a state or attribute is easy enough to be estimated or controlled.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>웬만큼 [웬ː만큼]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moderately; reasonably</dd><br>
<dd>허락되거나 받아들여지는 범위를 크게 넘지 않는 만큼.</dd><br>
<dd>In a degree that does not exceed the permitted or accepted bounds.</dd><br>
<dd>2. pretty; fairly; considerably</dd><br>
<dd>보통은 넘는 정도로.</dd><br>
<dd>To an extent above the average.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>엄정히 [엄정히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. strictly; rigidly</dd><br>
<dd>엄격하고 바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a strict and right manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fairly; impartially</dd><br>
<dd>날카롭고 공정하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a sharp and fair manner.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>어지간히 [어지간히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fairly; considerably</dd><br>
<dd>보통 수준이거나 그보다 조금 더 하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being equal to or slightly above the average level.</dd><br>
<dd>2. tolerably; passably</dd><br>
<dd>정도나 형편이 기준에 크게 벗어나지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a degree or situation being not totally against a standard.</dd><br>
<dd>3. fastidiously</dd><br>
<dd>성격이 만만하지 않아서 다루기가 어렵게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of someone being hard to deal with because he/she is not docile.</dd><br>
<dd>4. considerably; very much; greatly</dd><br>
<dd>보통 정도보다 훨씬 더.</dd><br>
<dd>Far more than the average level.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>십상 [십쌍]</dt><br>
<dd>fairly; perfectly</dd><br>
<dd>꼭 알맞게.</dd><br>
<dd>In an exactly adequate manner.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상당히 [상당히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fairly; pretty</dd><br>
<dd>수준이나 실력, 정도가 꽤 높게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which a level, degree, or ability is quite high.</dd><br>
<dd>2. considerably; pretty</dd><br>
<dd>어지간히 많이.</dd><br>
<dd>Quite a lot.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>무던히 [무던히]</dt><br>
<dd>fairly; quite</dd><br>
<dd>적당하거나 그보다 약간 더한 정도로.</dd><br>
<dd>Appropriately or a little more.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>당연히 [당연히]</dt><br>
<dd>naturally; fairly</dd><br>
<dd>이치로 보아 마땅히 그렇게.</dd><br>
<dd>Naturally and rightfully.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>꽤 [꽤]</dt><br>
<dd>quitely; fairly</dd><br>
<dd>예상이나 기대 이상으로 상당히.</dd><br>
<dd>Considerably well more than expected.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>깨끗이 [깨끄시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. clean</dd><br>
<dd>더럽지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>Not dirtily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. clearly</dd><br>
<dd>빛깔 등이 흐리지 않고 맑게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a color being clear, not vague.</dd><br>
<dd>3. neatly; tidily</dd><br>
<dd>가지런히 잘 정돈되고 단정하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being in good shape.</dd><br>
<dd>4. refreshingly</dd><br>
<dd>맛이나 느낌이 상쾌하고 개운하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of tasting refreshing or feeling fine.</dd><br>
<dd>5. completely; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>남은 것이나 흔적이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without leaving behind any leftovers or traces.</dd><br>
<dd>6. completely; flatly; frankly</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일에 집착하거나 구차하게 매달리지 않고 마음에 섭섭함이나 불만이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without clinging to something pathetically or without regrets or complaints.</dd><br>
<dd>7. completely; entirely</dd><br>
<dd>병을 앓고 난 뒤의 어떤 증상이나 힘든 일 뒤의 부작용 등이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any lingering symptoms or side effects after sickness or hardships.</dd><br>
<dd>8. fairly; honorably</dd><br>
<dd>마음씨나 행동이 떳떳하고 분명하며 올바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's mind or behavior being honorable, clear, and right.</dd><br>
<dd>9. innocently</dd><br>
<dd>마음이나 표정이 사납거나 험하지 않고 순수하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's mind or facial expression being pure, neither fierce nor violent.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>공평히 [공평히]</dt><br>
<dd>impartially; fairly</dd><br>
<dd>한쪽으로 치우치지 않고 모든 사람에게 고르게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that treats people equally without preferring one over others.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>공정히 [공정히]</dt><br>
<dd>fairly; justly</dd><br>
<dd>한쪽으로 치우치지 않고 올바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without being one-sided.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>공명정대히 [공명정대히]</dt><br>
<dd>fairly; unbiasedly</dd><br>
<dd>하는 일이나 태도가 한쪽으로 치우치거나 그릇됨이 없이 정당하고 떳떳하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting fairly and honorably and treating people without a preference, bias or impropriety.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>